South Africans are a funny lot with jokes coming thick and fast about the coronavirus. But maybe poking fun at a serious situation is how we cope in a crisis… Take President Cyril Ramaphosa’s elbow-bump greeting he demonstrated as he announced the lockdown. Within minutes, videos with fun music about his elbow bump had gone viral. Videos of people celebrating not working were a dime a dozen. As one boy said: “For the first time, I saw how much my parents hated their jobs.” Even the celebrities joined in. Popular comedian Skhumba told Ramaphosa to come to him for advice...